<sect1>
 <title>Communication Setup</title>
 <sect2>
   <title></title>
   <para>The EPICS control software only works with the below communication setup.</para>
   <simplelist type='horiz' columns='2'>
      <member>Bus Type</member>
      <member>RS-232</member>
      <member>Bits</member>
      <member>8</member>
      <member>Parity</member>
      <member>None</member>
      <member>Terminator</member>
      <member>CR+LF</member>
      <member>Flow Control</member>
      <member>None</member>
      <member>Baud Rate</member>
      <member>Tested at 9600.</member>
   </simplelist>
   <para>The tested hardware setup was a 8002+8515+Serial PIM. Use a straight through serial cable.</para>
 </sect2>
</sect1>

  <sect1>
       <title>Process Variable (PV) Names</title>
         <sect2>
           <title>Read Only PVs</title>
             <para>Note: {P} is dependent on how the software has been set-up.</para>
             <simplelist type='horiz' columns='2'>
             <member>{P}:TEMP</member>
             <member>Read the current water temperature (outflow)</member>
             <member>{P}:STATUS</member>
             <member>Read the current status bits.</member>
             <member>{P}:RESPONSE</member>
             <member>This contains the response from the execution of the COMMAND PV</member>
             </simplelist>
         </sect2>

         <sect2>
             <title>Write Only PVs</title>
             <simplelist type='horiz' columns='2'>
             <member>{P}:COMMAND</member>
             <member>Use this PV to send any command to the device (max 39 chars). If there is any response, it is placed in the RESPONSE PV.</member>
             </simplelist>
         </sect2>
  </sect1>

